Privacy Policy
Last Updated: 2024-09-21

1. Introduction
Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our Service.

2. Information We Collect
2.1. Personal Data
- Fitbit Account Information: When you connect your Fitbit account, we collect your user ID and access tokens.
- Activity Data: We collect activity data such as steps taken, distance traveled, and exercise sessions from your Fitbit account.
- Facebook User ID: We collect your Facebook Messenger ID to communicate with you through the bot.
2.2. Usage Data
We may collect information on how the Service is accessed and used, including timestamps and interaction data.

3. How We Use Your Information
3.1. To Provide and Maintain Our Service
Retrieve and analyze your Fitbit Data.
Send you notifications and messages based on your activity.
3.2. To Upload Data to Moojo Network
Your Fitbit Activity Data will be uploaded to the Moojo Network as part of the Service functionality.
3.3. To Improve Our Service
Analyze usage patterns to enhance user experience.

4. Disclosure of Your Information
4.1. Third-Party Service Providers
We may share your information with third-party service providers that perform services on our behalf, such as:
- Moojo Network: For uploading and processing your activity data.

4.2. Legal Obligations
We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.

5. Data Security
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information. However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.

6. Data Retention
We will retain your personal data only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy.

7. Your Rights
7.1. Withdraw Consent
You may withdraw your consent for us to access your Fitbit Data by disconnecting your Fitbit account.

7.2. Data Deletion
You may request the deletion of your data from our server by contacting us. Deletion of data from third-party services is subject to their privacy policy.

8. Children's Privacy
Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 18.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Last Updated" date.

10. Third-Party Links
